The '''Clay Golem''', also known as the '''MudGOL''' or '''MUDGOL'''<ref name="Enemy Identification Chart"/>, is an enemy in ''[[Final Fantasy]]''. First encountered as a [[fixed encounter]] in the [[Citadel of Trials]], they can later be encountered as regular enemies in the [[Waterfall Cavern]], [[Flying Fortress]] and [[Chaos Shrine (Final Fantasy)|Chaos Shrine]], where they may be encountered alongside the [[Mindflayer (Final Fantasy)|Mindflayer]] or [[Stone Golem (Final Fantasy)|Stone Golem]]. Despite their sturdy appearance, they have a very low [[Defense (stat)|Defense]] stat and can be defeated quite easily with physical attacks. Magical attacks do not work as well due to the Clay Golem's numerous resistances and high [[Magic Defense (stat)|Magic Defense]] stat.

Though they have poor defense, Clay Golems have reasonable HP and access to the [[Haste (Final Fantasy enemy ability)|Haste]] spell. Their attacks are fairly potent and can inflict [[Poison (Final Fantasy status)|Poison]], which can be exacerbated if they are allowed to Haste themselves.

